## Files

- `manifest.json`: run metadata, source, boundaries, stats, and file index.
- `schema.json`: JSONL field descriptions plus trace payload key sets.
- `raw/trace.jsonl`: snapshot copy of the resolved Codex rollout JSONL.
- `data/commands.jsonl`: tool call index.
- `data/results.jsonl`: structured result index.
- `data/messages.jsonl`: user and assistant message previews.
- `views/summary.md`: human-readable summary.
- `views/timeline.md`: compact chronological reading view.

Do not paste full `raw/trace.jsonl` or full JSONL indexes into context. Query them locally.
`manifest.json`, `data/commands.jsonl`, and `views/timeline.md` may contain local absolute paths from the trace; do not quote those paths in final reports.

