## Queries

```zsh
jq '.stats' manifest.json
jq -r 'select(.exit_code != null and .exit_code != 0) | [.line,.tool,.exit_code,.command_preview,.output_preview] | @tsv' data/results.jsonl
jq -r 'select(.role=="assistant") | [.line,.timestamp,.text_preview] | @tsv' data/messages.jsonl | tail -20
duckdb -no-init -json -c "SELECT r.line AS result_line, r.exit_code, c.tool, c.command_preview, r.output_preview FROM read_json_auto('data/results.jsonl') r LEFT JOIN read_json_auto('data/commands.jsonl') c USING (call_id) WHERE r.exit_code IS NOT NULL AND r.exit_code != 0 ORDER BY r.line;"
rg -n "pattern" data views
```

## Reading Order

1. Read `manifest.json`.
2. Read `views/summary.md`, then `views/timeline.md` if you need process detail.
3. Query `data/results.jsonl` for failures and `data/commands.jsonl` for command context.
4. Use `raw/trace.jsonl` only for line-level verification when an index preview is insufficient.
